        <profileDesc>
            <creation/>
            <abstract>
                <p>A collection of St George texts with fixed content and (more or less) stable
                    sequence in its manuscript transmission: after the <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6210MGTranslatio">Miracle of George: Andrew writes the Life after the saint’s death and after his body returned to Lydda</ref>, 12 miracles, classified by Budge as
                    canonical, follow in a (more or less fixed) sequence, (possibly?) assigned for
                    the <date ref="ethiocal:Hedar7">7th of Ḫǝdār</date>. All these texts were translated by <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/JCCVEYK8"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1930George"/><title level="m">George of Lydda, the Patron Saint of England: A Study of the Cultus of St. George in Ethiopia. The Ethiopic texts in facsimile edited for the first time from the manuscripts from Maḳdalâ now in the British Museum, with translations and an introduction</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest A. Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Co. Ltd.</publisher><date>1930</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">20</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">20</biblScope><note type="url">https://archive.org/details/stgeorge_20190327</note></bibl> based on <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BLorient691">London, British Library, BL Oriental 691</ref>.</p>
            </abstract>

