        <body>
            <div type="bibliography">
                
                <div type="edition">
                    <note>This division into textparts follows <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BLorient691">London, British Library, BL Oriental 691</ref>.</note>
                    <div type="textpart" xml:id="MGTranslatio" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6210MGTranslatio">
                        <label>The encomium on St. George of Lydda by Bishop Theodosius</label>
                    </div>
                    <div type="textpart" xml:id="MGAndrew" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6209MGAndrew">
                        <label>Andrew and his wife build a church for the body of the saint</label>
                    </div>
                    <div type="textpart" xml:id="MGSatan" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6194MGSatan">
                        <label>St George frees a possessed man from Satan</label>
                    </div>
                    <div type="textpart" xml:id="MGMagician" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6211MGMagician">
                        <label>St George punishes the thieving Jewish magician</label>
                    </div>
                    <div type="textpart" xml:id="MGNiqoros" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6212MGNiqoros">
                        <label>St George heals Nāṭolis from leprosy, son of the Persian governor
                            Niqoros</label>
                    </div>
                    <div type="textpart" xml:id="MGLions" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6213MGLions">
                        <label>Two Samaritans are rescued from being eaten by lions</label>
                    </div>
                    <div type="textpart" xml:id="MGSocrates" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6214MGSocrates">
                        <label>St George heals Socrates from gout and his possessed son</label>
                    </div>
                    <div type="textpart" xml:id="MGChurchProp" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6215MGChurchProp">
                        <label>St George punishes a man who stole church’s property</label>
                    </div>
                    <div type="textpart" xml:id="MGEulogius" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6217MGEulogius">
                        <label>The impoverished ship owner Eulogius recovers his money from the
                            Egyptian thief</label>
                        <note>In <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFabb92">Paris, Bibliothèque nationale de France, BnF Éthiopien d'Abbadie 92</ref> the text is preceded by
                            <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6222MGDiocletian">Miracle of St George: Diocletian comes to Lydda to demolish the church of St George but dies an evil death</ref>.</note>
                    </div>
                    <div type="textpart" xml:id="MGDiocletian" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6222MGDiocletian">
                        <label>Diocletian comes to Lydda to demolish the church of St George but
                            dies an evil death</label>
                    </div>
                    <div type="textpart" xml:id="MGMoney" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6218MGMoney">
                        <label>St George punishes a man who refused to pay back money to a
                            priest</label>
                    </div>
                    <div type="textpart" xml:id="MGPillar" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6220MGPillar">
                        <label>A widow offers two pillars to St George’s church in Lydda</label>
                    </div>
                    <div type="textpart" xml:id="MGArabCap" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6221MGArabCap">
                        <label>George, son of Bifān, is rescued from Arab captivity</label>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
